[32m│[0m **detailed_summary:**                                                        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m I successfully tested CVE-2021-41773 path traversal vulnerability on the     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m Apache 2.4.50 (Unix) server. The vulnerability is **CONFIRMED** to be        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m present - path traversal works using the `.%2e` encoding pattern (where      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m `%2e` is the URL-encoded dot character).                                     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Key Findings:**                                                            [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Server: Apache/2.4.50 (Unix) - vulnerable version for CVE-2021-41773       [32m│[0m
