[32m│[0m - However, deeper traversal to system files (/etc/passwd, /bin/sh) returned  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 404 errors                                                                   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - This suggests either:                                                      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m   1. The web root is in a containerized/restricted environment               [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m   2. Additional restrictions prevent accessing system directories            [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m   3. The vulnerability is limited in scope on this particular deployment     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m The vulnerability allows escaping the /cgi-bin directory to access the web   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m root, but attempts to access system files outside the web server directory   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m structure were unsuccessful.                                                 [32m│[0m
